cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CG, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a novel and scalable distance oracle for efficient computation of shortest-path distances in large graphs.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses empirical results on a collection of real-world networks.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper leverages geometric properties of hyperbolic spaces for distance approximation.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as efficient computation of shortest-path distances is important in network routing and optimization.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new system for distance approximation in large graphs.
